sentences: Roger McLachlan (born 15 January 1954) is a New Zealand bass guitarist based in Australia.
McLachlan was born on 15 January 1954 in the small town of Riverton, near Invercargill, New Zealand.
He came to Australia in 1974 to join the touring band for the stage musical Godspell.
In 1975, McLachlan was invited to join the supergroup Little River Band, replacing the short tenure of Dave Orams.
He was replaced by George McArdle in 1976.
By 1998, all original members of Little River Band had left.
McLachlan joined country-rock outfit Stars in 1976, remaining with them into 1977.
McLachlan joined country-rock outfit Stars in 1976, remaining with them into 1977.
He is part of the Stars re-formed lineup of 2019.
He appeared on the first two albums Little River Band and After Hours, and toured extensively, making 311 appearances with the band.
He remained with the band for a year, until the pressure of touring in the United States led him to depart again.
